label Final_Act_A_Natural_Death:

    scene bg walkToWork
    play music "CityAmbiance2.mp3"

    "{color=#01578F}Before the poor pathetic insect could finish his thought, he fell over. Dropping his work bag.{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}He began to convulse, and contort in front of the building. Was it in pain? Do flies have the receptors to feel pain? Is their pain even worth discussing?{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}People passed by him by like he didn't even exist.{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}After only a couple of minutes, which felt like hours to the fly, his natural form came into shape, his workbag to his right and his tie crumpled in front of him.{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}Of course, he could not recognize these items as they were. The only thing he had on his mind now was food and sex.{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}A simple mind, a simple life, a beauty to behold.{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}The fly noticed a figure holding something that he sensed contained sugar.{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}It was open, as free as him and he dived towards it at the speed of a kamikaze pilot.{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}And almost as quickly as he dove, he died instantly, boiled alive by the intense heat of the target of his desire contained.{/color}"

    "{color=#01578F}But is such an end so bad? it is an end of many a fly, and a much better way of life than some human beings could ever muster for themselves.{/color}"

    boss "Eh, I could use the extra protein."

